This is a spontaneous report from a non-clinical-study program Pfizer RXPathways from a contactable consumer. 
This 56-year-old female patient of unspecified ethnicity started to receive pregabalin (LYRICA) around 2000 after 
cancer at 200mg 2Xday for fibromyalgia and celecoxib (CELEBREX) near 2000 at 200 mg, 1x/day for arthritis. 
Medical history included cancer (colon/rectal), depression, many surgeries and she did not wish to change, even 
though it is a 2  hour trip to her office. She now believed she must change because after 2 car accidents she 
becomes frightened to ride for such long trips. Concomitant medications included bupropion from 2000 at 150 mg, 
1x/day for depression and fibromyalgia, fluoxetine from 2000 at 20 mg, 2x/day for depression, topiramate 
(TOPAMAX) from 2000 at 100 mg, 2x/day for migraines, ongoing clonazepam from 2000 at 0.5 mg, 3x/day, 
ongoing zolpidem tartrate (AMBIEN) from 2000 at 0.5 mg, 1x/day (nighty), ongoing omeprazole at 20 mg, 1x/day 
(nighty), ongoing montelukast sodium tablet from 2015 at 10 mg, 1x/day and ongoing estrogens esterified, 
methyltestosterone (COVARYX) 1.25-2.5mg 1X day. Patient stated that she had been out of her medication and 
was in pain. She still experienced pain (fibromyalgia, arthritis) from 2000 or before. Patient also stated that she has 
been in 2 head on car accidents since she has been off of the medication on (b) (6) and (b) (6)  and 
admission to hospital. She experienced completely bedridden without it/ completely bedridden (depression PTSD) 
from 2010 and admission to hospital. She was still taking pregabalin and celecoxib. Treatments were received for 
pain (fibromyalgia, arthritis), medication psychiatrist was received for completely bedridden (depression PTSD), Phy
therapy chiropractor was received for the event 2 head on car accidents. Outcome of the event pain (fibromyalgia, 
arthritis), 2 head on car accidents, completely bedridden (depression PTSD) was not recovered.
Follow-up (20Aug2015): New information reported from a contactable consumer included: patient data, suspect 
drug data, medical history, concomitant medications, event details, new event (PTSD, Depression), treatments and 
outcome.